28namespace webrtc {
29const int64_t PacedSender::kMaxQueueLengthMs = 2000;
30const float PacedSender::kDefaultPaceMultiplier = 2.5f;
31
32PacedSender::PacedSender(Clock* clock,
33 PacketRouter* packet_router,
34 RtcEventLog* event_log,
35 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* field_trials,
36 ProcessThread* process_thread)
37 : process_mode_(
38 (field_trials != nullptr &&
39 absl::StartsWith(field_trials->Lookup("WebRTC-Pacer-DynamicProcess"),
40 "Enabled"))
41 ? PacingController::ProcessMode::kDynamic
42 : PacingController::ProcessMode::kPeriodic),
43 pacing_controller_(clock,
44 packet_router,
45 event_log,
46 field_trials,
47 process_mode_),
48 clock_(clock),
49 process_thread_(process_thread) {
50 if (process_thread_)
51 process_thread_->RegisterModule(&module_proxy_, RTC_FROM_HERE);
52}
53
54PacedSender::~PacedSender() {
55 if (process_thread_) {
56 process_thread_->DeRegisterModule(&module_proxy_);
57 }
58}
59
60void PacedSender::CreateProbeCluster(DataRate bitrate, int cluster_id) {
61 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
62 return pacing_controller_.CreateProbeCluster(bitrate, cluster_id);
63}
64
65void PacedSender::Pause() {
66 {
67 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
68 pacing_controller_.Pause();
69 }
70
71 // Tell the process thread to call our TimeUntilNextProcess() method to get
72 // a new (longer) estimate for when to call Process().
73 if (process_thread_) {
74 process_thread_->WakeUp(&module_proxy_);
75 }
76}
77
78void PacedSender::Resume() {
79 {
80 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
81 pacing_controller_.Resume();
82 }
83
84 // Tell the process thread to call our TimeUntilNextProcess() method to
85 // refresh the estimate for when to call Process().
86 if (process_thread_) {
87 process_thread_->WakeUp(&module_proxy_);
88 }
89}

115void PacedSender::EnqueuePackets(
116 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets) {
117 {
118 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("webrtc"),
119 "PacedSender::EnqueuePackets");
120 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
121 for (auto& packet : packets) {
122 TRACE_EVENT2(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("webrtc"),
123 "PacedSender::EnqueuePackets::Loop", "sequence_number",
124 packet->SequenceNumber(), "rtp_timestamp",
125 packet->Timestamp());
126
127 RTC_DCHECK_GE(packet->capture_time_ms(), 0);
128 pacing_controller_.EnqueuePacket(std::move(packet));
129 }
130 }
131 MaybeWakupProcessThread();
132}

169int64_t PacedSender::TimeUntilNextProcess() {
170 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
171
172 Timestamp next_send_time = pacing_controller_.NextSendTime();
173 TimeDelta sleep_time =
174 std::max(TimeDelta::Zero(), next_send_time - clock_->CurrentTime());
175 if (process_mode_ == PacingController::ProcessMode::kDynamic) {
176 return std::max(sleep_time, PacingController::kMinSleepTime).ms();
177 }
178 return sleep_time.ms();
179}
180
181void PacedSender::Process() {
182 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
183 pacing_controller_.ProcessPackets();
184}
185
186void PacedSender::ProcessThreadAttached(ProcessThread* process_thread) {
187 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "ProcessThreadAttached 0x" << process_thread;
188 RTC_DCHECK(!process_thread || process_thread == process_thread_);
189}
190
191void PacedSender::MaybeWakupProcessThread() {
192 // Tell the process thread to call our TimeUntilNextProcess() method to get
193 // a new time for when to call Process().
194 if (process_thread_ &&
195 process_mode_ == PacingController::ProcessMode::kDynamic) {
196 process_thread_->WakeUp(&module_proxy_);
197 }
198}

200void PacedSender::SetQueueTimeLimit(TimeDelta limit) {

203 pacing_controller_.SetQueueTimeLimit(limit);
204 }
205 MaybeWakupProcessThread();
206}
